This paper deals with scheduling problems, which are typically studied in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves a matrix of processing times, which suggests a connection to matrix algorithms and computational complexity (cs.DM). The paper also mentions hardness of approximation, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the problem involves optimization and decision-making, which are studied in game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
